By Oladele Eniola Lagos – U.S pop star, Ariana Grande, has topped Billboard hot 100 for the fourth consecutive week with her song, ‘7 rings’ The Billboard Hot 100 is the music industry standard record chart in
the United States for songs, published weekly by Billboard magazine. Chart rankings are based on sales, both physical and digital, radio play, and online streaming in the United States. Grande’s songs, “Break up with your girlfriend, I’m bored’ and ‘Thank you, Next” were at No 2 and No 3, respectively. She became the first act to simultaneously claim the top three spots since the Beatles did that 55 years ago in 1964. Other songs to occupy the chat were, Halsey ‘Without you’, Post
Malone and Swag Lee ‘Sunflower’, Marshmello and Bastille, ‘Happier’
which occupied four, five and six positions, respectively. The other songs that completed the top 10 were, Travis Scott’s Sicko
mode, High hopes by Panic at the Disco, Wow by Post Malone and East side
by Benny Blanco, Hasley and Khalid. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that first No 1 song of the
Hot 100 was “Poor Little Fool” by Ricky Nelson, on Aug. 4, 1958. A new chart is compiled and officially released to the public by Billboard on Tuesday’s of every week. (NAN)